Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GUI
    This is an interface that will be implemented by all the GUI classes
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DatabaseDriver
    DatabaseDriver class to connect to database hosted in the cloud and read data to the java program
    EditRequestGUI
    This class represents the GUI for updating specific request It shows up after "Update chosen request" was clicked in the pull-down menu of "Actions".
    LabRequestTrackerRunner
    This is the runner class that runs the application
    LoginGUI
    This class represents the login GUI, it shows up at the beginning when user runs app.
    MainGUI
    This class represents the main GUI that showing the information of all requests It pops up after successful user login
    Request
    Request class represents all the information of the request in the database
    RequestBoard
    This RequestBoard class is used to read necessary data from the database create results for GUI to display
    RequestManager
    This RequestManager class is used when we need to submit new request, edit existing request, approve or reject a request, assign request, update request status It connects with database and Main, SubmitRequest, EditRequest GUI
    SubmitRequestGUI
    This class represents the GUI for submitting a new request It shows up after "Submit new request" was clicked in the pull-down menu of "Actions".
    UnitTestPartOne
    this class stores the first 10 unit tests We decided to have two separate unit test files because the database host we are currently using is a free one and only allows a certain number of connection calls, separating the unit tests would reduce the number of connection calls
    UnitTestPartTwo
    this class stores the remaining unit tests We decided to have two separate unit test files because the database host we are currently using is a free one and only allows a certain number of connection calls, separating the unit tests would reduce the number of connection calls
    User
    User class represents each user that has access to the system
    UserManager
    The UserManager class is used when we need to get user info, create new user, or update existing user info It creates a connection from DatabaseDriver, and connects to LoginGUI
